---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
import siteSettings from '../../../data/site-settings.json';
import { buildArticleSchema, buildBreadcrumbSchema, buildFAQSchema, buildWebSiteSchema } from '../../../lib/seo';

const title = 'Twice-yearly RV maintenance | What to do in spring and fall';
const description = 'Practical guide to twice-yearly RV maintenance: what to check in spring and fall for seals, roof areas, moisture, and watertightness.';
const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'Why maintain an RV twice a year?',
    answer: 'Two maintenance checks each year make it easier to review seals, roof areas, moisture signs, and exposed points before small weaknesses turn into expensive water intrusion. See our <a href="/en/services/maintenance/">RV maintenance service</a> if you want to book that work.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What should be checked in spring?',
    answer: 'In spring, focus on seals, roof areas, the membrane, openings, and any water or moisture signs that may have appeared after winter.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What should be checked in fall?',
    answer: 'In fall, the goal is to correct weak points before storage or harsher weather so a tired seal or small weakness does not let water in during the off-season. If moisture signs already look serious, start with an <a href="/en/services/inspection/">inspection</a>.'
  }
];
const schemas = [
  buildWebSiteSchema(),
  buildArticleSchema({
    headline: title,
    description,
    path: '/en/resources/twice-yearly-rv-maintenance/'
  }),
  buildFAQSchema(faqs),
  buildBreadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', path: '/en/' },
    { name: 'Resources' },
    { name: 'Twice-yearly maintenance' }
  ])
];
---

<Layout
  title={`${title} | Clinique du VR`}
  description={description}
  lang="en-CA"
  canonicalPath="/en/resources/twice-yearly-rv-maintenance/"
  frPath="/ressources/entretien-vr-deux-fois-par-an/"
  enPath="/en/resources/twice-yearly-rv-maintenance/"
  schemas={schemas}
  ogType="article"
>
  <Header lang="en" />
  <main>
    <section class="interior-hero">
      <div class="container interior-hero-grid">
        <div class="interior-hero-copy">
          <p class="interior-eyebrow">Practical resource</p>
          <h1>Recommended RV maintenance twice a year</h1>
          <p class="interior-lead">One maintenance check in spring and another in fall often provides the best balance between prevention, peace of mind, and protection against water intrusion.</p>
          <div class="hero-badges">
            <span>Spring + fall rhythm</span>
            <span>Seals, roof and membrane</span>
            <span>Prevention before repair</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="interior-hero-card">
          <div class="interior-hero-icon">
            <i class="fas fa-calendar-check"></i>
          </div>
          <h2>What this guide helps you plan</h2>
          <ul class="hero-checklist">
            <li>What to review before the season</li>
            <li>What to secure before storage</li>
            <li>When maintenance should become inspection instead</li>
          </ul>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="interior-section">
      <div class="container interior-body-grid">
        <article class="interior-content-main">
          <section class="interior-card">
            <h2>Why two maintenance checks a year</h2>
            <p class="interior-copy">An RV goes through temperature swings, UV exposure, rain, freezing weather, and road movement. Two checkpoints each year make it easier to spot tired seals, vulnerable roof areas, and early moisture signs before the issue gets worse.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="interior-card interior-card-alt">
            <h2>What to review in spring</h2>
            <ul>
              <li>Wall and roof seals.</li>
              <li>The membrane and sealing points.</li>
              <li>Water marks, moisture smells, or swelling.</li>
              <li>Vulnerable openings such as windows, vents, and joints.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="interior-card">
            <h2>What to prepare in fall</h2>
            <ul>
              <li>Correct dry, cracked, or lifting seals.</li>
              <li>Review roof condition before storage.</li>
              <li>Confirm that no area has started taking on water.</li>
              <li>Handle the useful corrections before harsher weather arrives.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="interior-card interior-card-alt">
            <h2>Common mistakes</h2>
            <p class="interior-copy">The most common mistake is waiting until there is major visible damage before acting. Another is looking only at appearance without confirming the actual condition of sealing zones, roof areas, and openings.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="interior-card">
            <h2>When maintenance makes more sense than inspection</h2>
            <p class="interior-copy">When seals and roof areas mostly show normal or expected wear, maintenance is often the right next step. If you are unsure of the source or already see moisture signs, inspection may be the better place to start.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="interior-card">
            <h2>A simple yearly rhythm</h2>
            <p class="interior-copy">The easiest rhythm to remember is usually one review in spring before the season and another in fall before harsher months. That helps keep a clear picture of the RV’s condition throughout the year.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="interior-card interior-card-alt">
            <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
            <div class="interior-faq-list">
              {faqs.map((item) => (
                <details class="interior-faq-item">
                  <summary><h3>{item.question}</h3></summary>
                  <p set:html={item.answer} />
                </details>
              ))}
            </div>
          </section>
        </article>

        <aside class="interior-side-panel">
          <div class="interior-side-card interior-side-card-primary">
            <h3>Need a quick opinion?</h3>
            <p>We can tell you whether your situation still looks like preventive maintenance or whether it already needs inspection or repair.</p>
            <a class="interior-side-button" href={`tel:${siteSettings.phone.href}`}>{siteSettings.phone.display}</a>
            <a class="interior-side-link" href={siteSettings.squareBookingUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book online</a>
          </div>

          <div class="interior-side-card">
            <h3>Related services</h3>
            <nav class="interior-service-nav" aria-label="Related services">
              <a href="/en/services/maintenance/"><i class="fas fa-screwdriver-wrench"></i><span>Maintenance</span></a>
              <a href="/en/services/inspection/"><i class="fas fa-clipboard-check"></i><span>Inspection</span></a>
              <a href="/en/services/repair/"><i class="fas fa-toolbox"></i><span>Repair</span></a>
              <a href="/en/realisations/"><i class="fas fa-images"></i><span>Projects</span></a>
            </nav>
          </div>

          <div class="interior-side-card">
            <h3>Service areas</h3>
            <nav class="interior-service-nav" aria-label="Service areas">
              <a href="/en/service-areas/"><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i><span>Outaouais</span></a>
              <a href="/en/service-areas/"><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i><span>Ottawa</span></a>
              <a href="/en/service-areas/"><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i><span>Laurentides</span></a>
            </nav>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer lang="en" />
</Layout>

<style>
  .interior-hero-copy h1 { max-width: 16ch; }
  .hero-badges { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.8rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  .hero-badges span { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; min-height: 44px; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-radius: 14px; background: var(--brand-gold); color: var(--brand-navy-dark); font-weight: 700; box-shadow: 0 10px 18px rgba(14, 31, 49, 0.14); }
  .hero-checklist { display: grid; gap: 0.65rem; padding-left: 1.2rem; color: var(--brand-muted); }
  .interior-card ul { display: grid; gap: 0.85rem; padding-left: 1.2rem; color: var(--brand-ink); }
  .interior-card li::marker, .hero-checklist li::marker { color: var(--brand-green); font-weight: 700; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-badges { gap: 0.55rem; }
    .hero-badges span { min-height: 38px; padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 12px; font-size: 0.88rem; }
  }
</style>
